What&#039;s remarkable about the image above is how fleeting this vista was (some number of years though it may have been, ca. 1964-67, 62-8 at the improbable outside, it&#039;s still blink of an eye in the Grand Scheme).  The Casa and Ems were never visible from Hill because of the Elks Lodge and other buildings along Olive.  
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Which makes the image below all the more amazing (ok, some people have a low threshold for amazing), as it was shot &lt;i&gt;after&lt;/i&gt; the demolition of the Casa/Ems but &lt;i&gt;before&lt;/i&gt; the &#039;69 removal of Angels Flight.  And the &lt;a href=&quot;/TheMonarch&quot; title=&quot;uni&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Union Bank&lt;/a&gt; peeking up is just too cool.  
&lt;/p&gt;
