&lt;img src=&quot;https://farm4.static.flickr.com/3410/3292797207_3a97dc68d3_o.gif&quot; alt=&quot;casamodel&quot; height=&quot;601&quot; width=&quot;575&quot; /&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
The Anhawo Motels.  The Amnano.  Annawo Motels.  The Annand Motels, that is, the Anhand.  I mean Ahwawo.   
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
No variations of these words exist in any of the usual places.  And the word &lt;i&gt;motel&lt;/i&gt; doesn&#039;t even show up in the directories until 1942.  So, for lack of a better expression, this is just damn weird.   
&lt;/p&gt;
